# Git submodules for this project.
#
# This template ships with NO active submodules. The entries below are COMMENTED-OUT
# EXAMPLES showing the convention the framework expects: vendor external repos in as
# submodules under the directories the docs reference (the active client/delivery code,
# the frozen legacy codebase, and the legacy SQL database).
#
# To use one: uncomment its block, replace the {PLACEHOLDER} values
# (see docs/architecture/project-placeholders.md), then run:
#   git submodule add <url> <path>     # first time, OR
#   git submodule update --init        # after cloning a repo that already declares them
#
# Leave this file with everything commented out if your project vendors nothing.

# --- Active client / delivery codebase (the existing implementation you extend) ---
# [submodule "csharp/{CLIENT-REPO-NAME}"]
# 	path = csharp/{CLIENT-REPO-NAME}
# 	url = {CLIENT-REPO-URL}
# 	branch = {CLIENT-REPO-BRANCH}

# --- Legacy codebase being migrated away from (frozen, read-only reference) ---
# [submodule "to_be_migrated_repo/{LEGACY-CODEBASE-DIR}"]
# 	path = to_be_migrated_repo/{LEGACY-CODEBASE-DIR}
# 	url = {LEGACY-CODEBASE-REPO-URL}
# 	branch = {LEGACY-CODEBASE-BRANCH}

# --- Legacy SQL database reference (frozen, read-only) ---
# [submodule "legacy-sql/{LEGACY-DB-NAME}"]
# 	path = legacy-sql/{LEGACY-DB-NAME}
# 	url = {LEGACY-DB-REPO-URL}
